---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="About — Project Flux Meridian" description="The story behind Flux Meridian — who we are, why we build free tools, and why we believe technology should work for everyone.">
    <!-- Hero -->
    <section class="hero">
        <div class="container hero__content">
            <h1>The Story Behind Flux Meridian</h1>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- L's Story -->
    <section class="section story">
        <div class="container story__content">
            <h2>Hi, I'm L</h2>
            <p>I'm L — they/them, based in Springfield, Missouri. I'm a systems thinker with ADHD, which means I see the world in patterns and connections and I can't stop building things. Sometimes that's a superpower. Sometimes it's three half-finished projects and a browser with forty tabs open.</p>
            <p>I couldn't find a tool that worked the way my brain does. Everything was either too rigid, too simple, or built for someone who didn't need it in the first place. So I built my own. We don't talk about versions 1.0 and 2.0. Third time's the charm — BRAIN 3.0 is the one that stuck.</p>
            <p>While I was heads-down building BRAIN, people in my life kept asking for tech help. And I realized something: there was nowhere safe to send them. Not everyone feels welcome walking into a repair shop or calling a help desk. So I started helping, one person at a time. That became FluxHelp.</p>
            <p>The same philosophy powers both: meet people where they are, build capacity instead of dependency. Whether it's a tool that does the executive function work for you, or a person sitting next to you showing you how to set up your email — the goal is the same. Make technology work for the person, not the other way around.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- The Mission -->
    <section class="section mission">
        <div class="container mission__content">
            <h2>What We Believe</h2>
            <p>Technology should work for everyone — not just the people who already understand it. Tools should respect the people using them, not exploit them. And help should be available to anyone, regardless of what they look like, where they live, or how much they know.</p>
            <p>BRAIN is open source under AGPL-3.0. FluxHelp is free, no strings. This isn't a business model — it's a promise. If we can't do it without charging the people who need it most, we're doing it wrong.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- What's Next -->
    <section class="section next">
        <div class="container next__content">
            <h2>Where We're Going</h2>
            <p>Flux Meridian is incorporating as a nonprofit. BRAIN is actively in development with a public roadmap. FluxHelp is growing, one person at a time. The work is just getting started — but the foundation is solid and the mission hasn't wavered.</p>
            <a href="https://github.com/WilliM233/brain3" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="next__link">See our work on GitHub &rarr;</a>
        </div>
    </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
    /* ===== Hero (short — heading only) ===== */
    .hero {
        background: linear-gradient(180deg, var(--bg-deep) 0%, var(--bg-mid) 100%);
        padding-block: var(--space-3xl) var(--space-xl);
    }

    .hero__content {
        text-align: center;
        max-width: 720px;
        margin-inline: auto;
    }

    /* ===== Shared section prose styling ===== */
    .story__content,
    .mission__content,
    .next__content {
        max-width: 720px;
        margin-inline: auto;
    }

    .story__content h2,
    .mission__content h2,
    .next__content h2 {
        margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
    }

    .story__content p,
    .mission__content p,
    .next__content p {
        color: var(--text-secondary);
        line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
        margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
    }

    /* ===== Mission — subtle background shift ===== */
    .mission {
        background: var(--bg-mid);
    }

    /* ===== What's Next ===== */
    .next__link {
        display: inline-block;
        margin-top: var(--space-sm);
        font-family: var(--font-display);
        font-weight: 600;
    }
</style>
